# Database — Drizzle (Postgres)

Stack: Postgres + Drizzle ORM. Server-side queries called directly from Server Components and server actions; Client Components reach data through API routes only when interactivity demands it.

## Drizzle client
- Server-side only: import `db` from `src/lib/db/client.ts`.
- Schema lives in `src/lib/db/schema.ts` (one file per table or grouped by domain).
- Never import `db` or anything from `src/lib/db/` in a Client Component.
- Never instantiate `postgres()` / `drizzle()` outside `src/lib/db/client.ts`.

```ts
// src/lib/db/client.ts
import { drizzle } from "drizzle-orm/postgres-js"
import postgres from "postgres"
import * as schema from "./schema"

const client = postgres(process.env.DATABASE_URL!, { prepare: false })
export const db = drizzle(client, { schema })
```

## Queries
- Use Drizzle's query builder or the `db.query.*` relational API — never write raw SQL outside of migrations.
- Select explicit columns: `.select({ id: posts.id, title: posts.title })` — never select the whole row by default.
- Always scope by `userId` — Drizzle has no equivalent of RLS, ownership is your job.
- For single-row lookups, return `null` when nothing matches — don't throw.
- Wrap server-side fetches in `React.cache()` so the same query inside one request hits the DB once:

```ts
// src/lib/db/queries/posts.ts
import { cache } from "react"
import { and, eq } from "drizzle-orm"
import { db } from "@/lib/db/client"
import { posts } from "@/lib/db/schema"

export const getPostById = cache(async (id: string, userId: string) => {
  const [post] = await db
    .select({ id: posts.id, title: posts.title, body: posts.body })
    .from(posts)
    .where(and(eq(posts.id, id), eq(posts.userId, userId)))
    .limit(1)

  return post ?? null
})
```

## Data flow

**Default (Server Component):**
```
Server Component
  └─ getPostById()  (React.cache wrapped)
       └─ Drizzle query
            └─ Postgres
```

**When client interactivity requires it** (polling, infinite scroll, optimistic updates):
```
Client Component
  └─ useQuery / useMutation hook (src/hooks/use-*.ts)
       └─ fetch('/api/...')
            └─ Route handler
                 └─ Drizzle query
```

- One hook per resource × operation: `usePosts`, `usePost(id)`, `useCreatePost`, etc.
- The hook owns cache invalidation — components stay declarative.
- Parse the `{ data } | { error }` shape from `04-api`; throw on `!res.ok` so React Query surfaces the error.

## Types
Drizzle infers row types from the schema. Re-export them — never redefine.

```ts
// src/lib/db/types.ts
import type { posts } from "./schema"

export type Post = typeof posts.$inferSelect
export type NewPost = typeof posts.$inferInsert
```

## Migrations
- Managed by `drizzle-kit`. Config in `drizzle.config.ts`; migrations in `drizzle/`.
- Edit `src/lib/db/schema.ts`, then:
  ```bash
  pnpm drizzle-kit generate   # writes a new SQL migration to drizzle/
  pnpm drizzle-kit migrate    # applies pending migrations
  ```
- Never edit a generated migration by hand — change the schema and regenerate.
- Never mutate the database directly in a GUI.
